President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Peter S. Silva as Assistant Administrator for Water Programs at the Environmental Protection Agency, and Martha Johnson as Administrator of the General Services Administration. Peter S. Silva is a Civil Engineer with experience in water and wastewater fields, and Martha Johnson has held various leadership roles in organizations such as Computer Sciences Corporation and the Department of Labor. Both nominees are expected to bring dedication, intelligence, and expertise to their positions as they work to address the challenges facing the nation.